org.sakaiproject.section.api.coursemanagement

Interface LearningContext

  • All Known Subinterfaces:
    Course, CourseSection
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    CourseImpl, CourseImpl, CourseSectionImpl, CourseSectionImpl, LearningContextImpl, LocalSectionModel

    public interface LearningContext
    A LearningContext is an abstract grouping of users in an academic environment. Examples include CourseOfferings, Sections, and could potentially include departments and colleges. For Sakai 2.1, only CourseOfferings and CourseSections are LearningContexts. A student can be enrolled in any learning context.
    Author:
    Josh Holtzman
